You can use the following CSS code to set the font size to 20px:

```css
font-size: 20px;
```

You can also use the following code to set the font size for a specific element, for example, a paragraph:

```css
p {
  font-size: 20px;
}
```

Or, if you want to set the font size for all elements on your webpage, you can use the following code:

```css
* {
  font-size: 20px;
}
```

Note: The asterisk (*) is a wildcard character in CSS that selects all elements on the webpage.
